White shepherd dog breeds of Europe

images.description:
Pyrenees mountain dog, aka Great Pyrenees dog, has been a favourite breed for the shepherds in the Pyrenees mountain range, stretching across the border between France and Spain.

From 1675 the breed was a favorite of the Grand Dauphin and other members of the French aristocracy. Later in the 17th century, King Louis XIV's court adopted the Great Pyrenees as the Royal Dog of France.

The breed features in the children's story Belle and Sebastien

Pastore maremmano abruzzese (Maremma shepherd dog) is a breed native of mountainous region of Abruzzo, in central Italy, where it has been used by shepherds for centuries during the bi yearly migration of the flocks between the mountain pastures of Abruzzo and the lowland ones of Apulia. 

Maremma shepherd dogs have been used in Australia to guard an endangered colony of penguins from attacks from foxes.
Tatra shepherd dogs. The breed takes its name from the Tatra mountains, a mountain range in Southern Poland and Slovakia.

“I’ll keep your pillow warm until you get back”

This is Ringo (left) and I adopted him over a week ago. He is originally from California where his owners physically abused him and then was saved from euthanasia by a woman who brought him to a shelter here in Michigan. Over the last couple of years he has been in different foster homes and was even kenneled for 5 months when he had no where to go.
I was a little worried about adoption because I have a small child and other pets.
He is the sweetest boy and very snuggley! We have had a few bumps in the road so far with him marking the entire house but we are working with the foster mom and a trainer to get that under control.
You heard of lap dogs right? Well Honeybun wants to be a neck / chest dog. I got to go pee, but I don't want to wake her up.

“Mummy and daddy have gone out and left me here”.
We lost little Beano today. Having three legs just wasn’t doing his spine any good. I’ve never been so physically and emotionally exhausted.
The good thing is, after having a rough start to life, he had two years of never ending fun and joy. He was always there, staring deep into your soul with those little brown glass marbles for eyes, and then he’d flop onto you with all his weight, look up and say “I love you”. He kept us together at our lowest moments.  Thanks for reading.
